Author::::Deviantinc
DateTime::::2016-03-11T11:24:00Z
I don't think I'm saying every branch of maths will be useful to everyone and every job. But I do think that in any job or for any person there is a branch of maths that would be useful if they understood it enough to be able to apply it. But you cannot know in advance which branch that will be, so it is advisable to teach a broad range of maths. You may not have had to factorise a quadratic, but some people might need to. And furthermore, factorising a quadratic isn't really a skill useful in itself, but is a very useful for learning other formula rearranging techniques, that someone may need to use when trying to apply a formula someone else has produced in a non-standard way. 



